caption.p:
Tornado chart showing the correlation coefficients of input parameters modeled as an uncertainty distribution with the probability that at least one piglet will be infected (P
inf
). Results are only shown for input parameters with a correlation coefficient ≥|0.1|. RVplasma = reduction of virus concentration after separating plasma from red blood cell fraction; VCanimalT = virus concentration in the blood of an infected animal on dpi t; ID50 = infectious dose at which 50% of the animals is infected; Tinf = infectious period.
